\begin_layout Standard
Next, we check the number of the subhalos which have different 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc,first}}.$
\end_inset

 Among all the subhalos (whose host halo masses are greater than 
\begin_inset Formula $10^{14}h^{-1}{\rm M_{\odot}}$
\end_inset

), 
\begin_inset Formula $43.1\%$
\end_inset

 of them have different 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc,first}}$
\end_inset

.
 Among those subhalos, 
\begin_inset Formula $84.2\%$
\end_inset

 have 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc,first}}>0.4$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $17.2\%$
\end_inset

 are accreted again to have 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}>0.4$
\end_inset

.
 This implies that most of the subhalos are accreted again after 
\begin_inset Formula $z=0.4$
\end_inset

.
 The left panel of Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:hist_z_acc"

\end_inset

 shows the distribution of 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc,first}}$
\end_inset

 for the subhalos with 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}\neq z_{{\rm acc,first}}$
\end_inset

.
 The figure shows that many subhalos are accreted around 
\begin_inset Formula $z=0.5-1.0$
\end_inset

 for the first time and move out from their host halos.
 Then, they come back after 
\begin_inset Formula $z=0.5$
\end_inset

.
 The right panel of Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:hist_z_acc"

\end_inset

 shows the difference between 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc,first}}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

 for the same subhalos.
 Since it takes 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta z=0.25$
\end_inset

 to complete one orbiting (based on Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:halo_centric1"

\end_inset

), this figure shows that many subhalos repeat moving out and coming back
 in for several times.
\end_layout

