	filename plots_Cluster/scatter_z_vmaxLoss2.pdf
	lyxscale 70
	width 50text%

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "fig:correlation"

\end_inset

Left: Correlation between the accretion redshift 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

 and the retained mass of the subhalos 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{{\rm vir}}/m_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

 at 
\begin_inset Formula $z=0$
\end_inset

.
 Right: correlation between the accretion redshift 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

 and the retained maximum circular velocity of the subhalos 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{{\rm max,sub}}/V_{{\rm max,acc}}$
\end_inset

 at 
\begin_inset Formula $z=0$
\end_inset

.
 The red dashed lines are the median accretion redshifts as a function of
 the retained mass.
 For the right panel, we scale the halo mass to 
\begin_inset Formula $m^{1/3}$
\end_inset

.
 The cyan dashed line is the median accretion redshift as a function of
 the retained maximum circular velocity.
 The slopes for both dashed lines are almost the same up to 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}<0.6$
\end_inset

 and deviate after that due to the large scatter in the 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{{\rm vir}}/m_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

(or 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{{\rm max,sub}}/V_{{\rm acc,sub}}$
\end_inset

)-
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

 relation.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:hist_correlation"

\end_inset

 shows the distribution of 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

 as a function of 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{{\rm vir}}/m_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

 (split into 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{{\rm vir}}/m_{{\rm acc}}>10^{-0.25}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $10^{-0.5}-10^{-0.25}$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $<10^{-0.5}$
\end_inset

).
 While the range of 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

 for each retained mass bin is wide, each distribution shows clear peaks
 in the 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

 distributions, which indicates that 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{{\rm vir}}/m_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

 are nicely correlated.
 The median values for each subsample are 0.133 for 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{{\rm vir}}/m_{{\rm acc}}>10^{-0.25}$
\end_inset

, 0.493 for 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{{\rm vir}}/m_{{\rm acc}}=10^{-0.5}-10^{-0.25}$
\end_inset

, and 0.894 for 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{{\rm vir}}/m_{{\rm acc}}<10^{-0.5}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

