\end_inset

.
 Different colors correspond to different accretion redshifts.
 While the subhalos which are accreted after 
\begin_inset Formula $z=0.5$
\end_inset

 (or the subhalos which have not lost much mass) do not exhibit any difference
 in the spatial distribution for the high/low-concentration host halos,
 the subhalos which are accreted before 
\begin_inset Formula $z=0.5$
\end_inset

 have similar inner distribution but different outer distributions.
 The subhalos in the high concentration host halos show steeper decrease
 as the distance gets closer to the virial radius (how can I describe this
 more clearly?) 
