LatexCommand label
name "fig:subhaloMassFn"

\end_inset

Unevolved subhalo mass functions (left) and evolved subhalo mass functions
 (right) at 
\begin_inset Formula $z=0$
\end_inset

.
 We use the host halos whose masses are greater than 
\begin_inset Formula $10^{14}h^{-1}{\rm Mpc}$
\end_inset

 and split them based on their concentrations.
 The blue lines are the subhalos whose host halos have high concentration,
 while the green lines are for low concentration.
 (Remake the figure without plotting the circles+ I should choose host halos
 with more mass range; also should I use MD instead of Bolshoi?)
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

