reference "fig:nfw"

\end_inset

 compares the NFW profiles and the radial profiles of the subhalos with
 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}>0.5$
\end_inset

 for the host halos split into 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

high/low-concentration
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 To compute the NFW profiles, we use the median concentration of each sample;
 4.767 for the low-concentration halos and 7.446 for the high-concentration
 halos.
 We see the similar trend on the outer region that the subhalos in the low-conce
ntration halos have higher amplitude than the ones for the high-concentration
 halos.
 Overall profiles between NFW profiles and subhalos are consistent with
 the finding in XXX [
\color red
nagai_kravtsov
\color inherit
]
